  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, when internal/external plugins are trying to write/read in File Explorer, when no workspace available, the FileManager is not creating the file/folder but throwing an error.\r\nOur plugins are not handling this error but either doing nothing or printing an error in the console. No feedback to the user.\r\nI see 3 options:\r\n\r\n1. handle that it FileManager - simply create a workspace on demand\r\n2. handle that it FileManager - FilManager is auto-creating a new workspace when the last one is deleted\r\n3. update all internal/external plugins that writing a file/folder in File Manager and handle the error case by case\r\n",
